import folium
import pandas as pd
from geopy.distance import geodesic

# #    ()
# schools_data = [
#     {"name": "1", "lat": 37.500123, "long": 127.033456},
#     {"name": "2", "lat": 37.512345, "long": 127.045678}
# ]

# #    ()
# students_data = [
#     {"lat": 37.505678, "long": 127.037890},
#     {"lat": 37.518901, "long": 127.051234},
#     # ...
# ]

#  
# schools_df = pd.DataFrame(schools_data)
# students_df = pd.DataFrame(students_data)

#  
m = folium.Map(location=[37.437793, 126.575861], zoom_start=11,tiles="Stamen Terrain")

#   
for idx, school in df_schools.iterrows():
    folium.Marker([school["lat"], school["long"]], popup=school["name"], icon=folium.Icon(color='red')).add_to(m)

#   
for idx, student in df_students.iterrows():
    folium.CircleMarker([student["lat"], student["long"]], radius= student[""]/10, color= 'blue', fill = True).add_to(m)

#    1.5km   
for idx, school in df_schools.iterrows():
    folium.Circle(
        location=[school["lat"], school["long"]],
        radius=1500,  # 1.5km   
        color='red',
    ).add_to(m)

#     1.5km      
for idx, school in df_schools.iterrows():
    school_position = (school["lat"], school["long"])
    students_within_radius = df_students.apply(lambda student: geodesic(school_position, (student["lat"], student["long"])).kilometers <= 1.5, axis=1)
#     print(f"{school['name']}   1km    : {students_within_radius.sum()}")
    total_population = df_students[students_within_radius][""].sum()
    print(f"{school['name']}   1.5km     : {total_population}")
    
#

import folium
import pandas as pd
from geopy.distance import geodesic

# #    ()
# schools_data = [
#     {"name": "1", "lat": 37.500123, "long": 127.033456},
#     {"name": "2", "lat": 37.512345, "long": 127.045678}
# ]

# #    ()
# students_data = [
#     {"lat": 37.505678, "long": 127.037890},
#     {"lat": 37.518901, "long": 127.051234},
#     # ...
# ]

#  
# schools_df = pd.DataFrame(schools_data)
# students_df = pd.DataFrame(students_data)

#  
m = folium.Map(location=[37.437793, 126.575861], zoom_start=11, tiles="Stamen Terrain")

#   
for idx, school in df_schools_pre.iterrows():
    folium.Marker([school["lat"], school["long"]], popup=school[""], icon=folium.Icon(color='red')).add_to(m)

#   
for idx, student in df_students.iterrows():
    folium.CircleMarker([student["lat"], student["long"]], radius= student[""]/10, color= 'blue', fill = True).add_to(m)

#    1.5km   
for idx, school in df_schools_pre.iterrows():
    folium.Circle(
        location=[school["lat"], school["long"]],
        radius=1500,  # 1.5km   
        color='red',
#         fill=True,
#         fill_opacity=0.2
    ).add_to(m)

#     1.5km      
for idx, school in df_schools_pre.iterrows():
    school_position = (school["lat"], school["long"])
    students_within_radius = df_students.apply(lambda student: geodesic(school_position, (student["lat"], student["long"])).kilometers <= 1.5, axis=1)
#     print(f"{school['name']}   1km    : {students_within_radius.sum()}")
    total_population = df_students[students_within_radius][""].sum()
    print(f"{school['']}   1.5km     : {total_population}")
